"{\"uid\": \"canberratimes.com.au-story-8726399-tom-cruise-performs-abseiling-stunt-to-close-olympics\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Your digital subscription includes access to content from all our websites in your region.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 90, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Access unlimited news content and The Canberra Times app.\", \"from\": 92, \"to\": 149, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 126, \"end\": 144, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Canberra_Times\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"The Canberra Times\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q234460\", \"Q11032\", \"Q1092563\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Canberra_Times\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Canberra_Times\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Premium subscribers also enjoy interactive puzzles and access to the digital version of our print edition - Today's Paper.\", \"from\": 150, \"to\": 272, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Tom Cruise has abseiled down into the State de France during the closing ceremony at the Paris Olympics.\", \"from\": 274, \"to\": 378, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 274, \"end\": 284, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_Cruise\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Tom Cruise\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_Cruise\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_Cruise\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Loginor signup to continue reading  The Mission: Impossible actor performed one of his trademark stunts at Sunday's ceremony as he slid 35m down a rope from the venue's roof as part of the handover to Los Angeles for the 2028 Games.\", \"from\": 380, \"to\": 612, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 581, \"end\": 592, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"score\": 0.9999999999822649, \"rank\": 1.7905493742129048e-11, \"text\": \"Los Angeles\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Tom was seen greeting athletes present at the ceremony before landing and taking the Olympic flag away on a motorbike.\", \"from\": 614, \"to\": 732, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"A pre-recorded segment then showed the star carrying the flag back to the US on a plane before he draped it over the Hollywood sign.\", \"from\": 734, \"to\": 866, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 808, \"end\": 810, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.8480789623774567, \"rank\": 0.10947236173811106, \"text\": \"US\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 851, \"end\": 865, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hollywood_Sign\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Hollywood sign\", \"types\": [\"Q41176\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hollywood_Sign\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hollywood_Sign\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A report from TMZ earlier this month revealed the Los Angeles element of the stunt was filmed in March and insiders admitted they had expected the Hollywood star to be spotted and the information to be leaked beforehand.\", \"from\": 868, \"to\": 1088, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 882, \"end\": 885, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/TMZ\", \"score\": 0.9999998020453145, \"rank\": 1.9795452115343638e-07, \"text\": \"TMZ\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/TMZ\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/TMZ\"}, {\"begin\": 918, \"end\": 929, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"score\": 0.9999999999822649, \"rank\": 1.7905493742129048e-11, \"text\": \"Los Angeles\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\"}, {\"begin\": 1015, \"end\": 1024, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cinema_of_the_United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999999992951416, \"rank\": 7.046994213377677e-10, \"text\": \"Hollywood\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cinema_of_the_United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cinema_of_the_United_States\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Cruise is said to have been the driving force behind the spectacle and approached the International Olympic Committee (IOC) himself about doing a series of stunts to bring the Paris and Los Angeles Games together.\", \"from\": 1090, \"to\": 1303, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1176, \"end\": 1213, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"International Olympic Committee (IOC)\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}, {\"begin\": 1176, \"end\": 1213, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"International Olympic Committee (IOC)\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}, {\"begin\": 1266, \"end\": 1271, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999995161488, \"rank\": 4.839837386421456e-10, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Meanwhile, the ceremony also featured performances from H.E.R., Red Hot Chilli Peppers, Billie Eilish as well as Snoop Dogg and Dr. Dre - with the 'Fight For You' hitmaker singing US national anthem 'The Star-Spangled Banner' in the stadium and the latter quartet performing from Venice Beach in LA.\", \"from\": 1305, \"to\": 1604, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1361, \"end\": 1367, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/H.E.R.\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 9.639273237306744e-35, \"text\": \"H.E.R.\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q483501\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/H.E.R.\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/H.E.R.\"}, {\"begin\": 1369, \"end\": 1391, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Red_Hot_Chili_Peppers\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Red Hot Chilli Peppers\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q215380\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Red_Hot_Chili_Peppers\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Red_Hot_Chili_Peppers\"}, {\"begin\": 1418, \"end\": 1428, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Snoop_Dogg\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Snoop Dogg\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Snoop_Dogg\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Snoop_Dogg\"}, {\"begin\": 1485, \"end\": 1503, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Star-Spangled_Banner\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"US national anthem\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Star-Spangled_Banner\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Star-Spangled_Banner\"}, {\"begin\": 1585, \"end\": 1597, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Venice,_Los_Angeles\", \"score\": 0.9999999752494663, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Venice Beach\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Venice,_Los_Angeles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Venice,_Los_Angeles\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The event also marked a celebration of the past fortnight of sporting action in Paris and IOC president Thomas Bach quipped that the Olympics had been \\\"Seine-sational\\\".\", \"from\": 1606, \"to\": 1774, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1686, \"end\": 1691, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999995161488, \"rank\": 4.839837386421456e-10, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 1696, \"end\": 1699, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.215322705716059e-22, \"text\": \"IOC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}, {\"begin\": 1710, \"end\": 1721, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_Bach\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Thomas Bach\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_Bach\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_Bach\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He said: \\\"The Olympic Games Paris 2024 were a celebration of the athletes and sport at its best.\", \"from\": 1776, \"to\": 1872, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The first Olympic Games delivered fully under our Olympic Agenda reforms: younger, more urban, more inclusive, more sustainable.\", \"from\": 1873, \"to\": 2001, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The first ever Olympic Games with full gender parity.\", \"from\": 2002, \"to\": 2055, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"These were sensational Olympic Games from start to finish - or dare I say: SEINE-sational Olympic Games.\", \"from\": 2057, \"to\": 2162, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"The Olympic Games Paris 2024 were Olympic Games of a new era.\\\"\", \"from\": 2164, \"to\": 2227, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Australian Associated Press  Daily  Today's top stories curated by our news team.\", \"from\": 2229, \"to\": 2310, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Also includes evening update.\", \"from\": 2311, \"to\": 2340, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"As it happ